===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|十|又|ls=ic|t1=ten|t2=hand}} – ten ''chi'' ({{zh-l|*尺}}) is one ''zhang'' ({{lang|zh|丈}}). Similar but unrelated to [[支]].

===Etymology===
;"gentleman, older man, husband"
:From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*C-rjaŋ||uncle, superior}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, STEDT; compare {{cog|sit-pro|*tVŋ||upper part, rise, raise, top, summit}}). Cognate with {{och-l|尚}} "upwards", {{cog|bo|ཨ་ཞང||maternal uncle}}, {{cog|my|အရှင်|t=master, lord}}, etc.
;"unit of measurement"
:From {{der|zh|sit-pro|-}}, compare {{cog|lus|'''ṭâng''' " kai||to measure (v.), a measure (n.) from the tip of the middle finger from one side to a spot between the breast bone and the other side's armpit}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}})

